{"title_page": "Arena of Valor", "text_new": "{{Infobox video game\n| title = Arena of Valor\n| image = Arena of Valor logo.png\n| developer = [[Tencent]], [[TiMi Studios]], [[Garena]]\n| publisher = [[Tencent]] (Europe, North America, Latin America, Australasia, Middle East - North Africa, South Asia, Russia)\n\n[[Garena]] (Taiwan, Macau, Hong Kong, & Southeast Asia)\n\n[[Netmarble]] (South Korea)\n\n[[DeNA]] (Japan)\n\nSixjoy (India) (Formerly)\nProxima Beta (Europe) (Formerly)\n| composer = {{ubl|Jeff Broadbent|Matthew Carl Earl|[[Hans Zimmer]]}}\n| platforms = [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[iOS]], [[Nintendo Switch]]\n| released = '''Android, iOS'''{{Video game release|[[China|CHN]]|November 26, 2015 ([[Honor of Kings|HoK]])|[[Taiwan|TWN]]|October 14, 2016|[[Vietnam|VN]]|November 21, 2016|[[Thailand|TH]]|December 26, 2016|[[South Korea|KR]]|April 26, 2017|[[Indonesia|IDN]]|June 6, 2017|EU|August 10, 2017|[[Malaysia|MY]], [[Singapore|SG]], & [[Philippines|PH]]|October 17, 2017|[[North America|NA]] & [[Latin America|LATAM]]|December 19, 2017|[[India|IND]]|March 1, 2018|[[Australasia|AU]], [[Brunei|BRU]], [[Myanmar|MMR]], [[Laos|LA]], & [[Cambodia|CBD]]|June 28, 2018|[[Japan|JPN]]|November 30, 2018|[[MENA]], [[South Asia|SA]], & [[Russia|RU]]|April 16, 2020}}\n\n\n'''Nintendo Switch''' {{Video game release|WW|September 25, 2018}}\n| display = ''' Alternative Name On Various Servers'''{{ubl|Thailand Server - ''Realm of Valor''/''RoV'' (First official English name, but this server still use it till today)|Indonesian Server - ''Mobile Arena'' (Formerly before renamed to ''Arena of Valor'')|Europe Server - ''Strike of Kings'' (Formerly before renamed to ''Arena of Valor'')|Vietnam Server - ''Li\u00ean Qu\u00e2n'' (Roughly translated to ''Arena of Valor'' in [[English language|English]])|Korean Server - ''Penta Storm''/\ud39c\ud0c0\uc2a4\ud1b0 (''Penta Seutom'')|Taiwan Server - ''Legendary Showdown''/\u50b3\u8aaa\u5c0d\u6c7a (''Chu\u00e1nshu\u014d Du\u00ecju\u00e9'')|Japan Server - ''Legendary Showdown''/\u4f1d\u8aac\u5bfe\u6c7a (''Densetsu Taiketsu'')}}\n| genre = [[Multiplayer online battle arena]]\n| modes = [[Multiplayer]]\n}}\n\n'''''Arena of Valor''''' ('''''AoV''''') ({{zh|s=\u50b3\u8aaa\u5c0d\u6c7a|p=Chu\u00e1nshu\u014d Du\u00ecju\u00e9}}), formerly '''''Realm of Valor''''' then '''''Strike of Kings''''', is an international adaptation of ''[[Wangzhe Rongyao|Honor of Kings]]'' ({{zh|s=\u738b\u8005\u8363\u8000|p=W\u00e1ngzh\u011b R\u00f3ngy\u00e0o}}), also known in English unofficial translations as '''''Kings of Glory''''', a [[multiplayer online battle arena]] developed by [[TiMi Studios]] and published by [[Tencent Games]] for [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[iOS]] and [[Nintendo Switch]] for markets outside mainland China. As of September 2018, the game has grossed over {{US$|140 million|long=no}} outside China.<ref>{{cite news |last=Spannbauer |first=Adam |title=Arena of Valor Revenue Clears $140 Million Outside China |url=https://sensortower.com/blog/arena-of-valor-revenue-outside-china |work=Sensor Tower |date=September 17, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Gameplay ==\n''Arena of Valor'' is a [[3D computer graphics|3D]], [[Third-person (video games)|third-person]], [[multiplayer online battle arena]] (MOBA) style game for mobile. The game has multiple modes, with the main three being Grand Battle, Valley Skirmish and Abyssal Clash.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://samurai-gamers.com/arena-of-valor/game-modes-overview/|title=Arena of Valor (AoV) - Game Modes Overview (Abyssal Clash, Hook Wars, etc.)|last=Green|date=2018-02-20|website=SAMURAI GAMERS|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-03}}</ref> Players compete in these matches which on average last for around 12 - 18 minutes. Players aim to destroy turrets on the map, in order to destroy the core.\n\nThe overall gameplay of ''Arena of Valor'' highly resembles a game called ''[[League of Legends]]'', a MOBA game developed and published by [[Riot Games]], which is a subsidiary of Tencent.\n\nPlayers control characters, referred to as heroes, and each of these heroes have a unique set of abilities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.arenaofvalor.com/|title=Arena of Valor|website=Arena of Valor|language=en|access-date=2019-02-03}}</ref> Heroes start the game at a low level, and can earn level up in various ways. Killing non-player creatures such as minions or monsters, defeating other players, destroying structures, passively through time and through special items that can be purchased through the shop. These actions also increase XP the player has, making them more powerful. The items purchased do not carry over matches, and therefore all players are on equal footing at the start of the match.\n\nMatches give players rewards, such as gold, which can then be used to buy a variety of heroes, or arcana.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mobilegamerhub.com/arena-of-valor/tips-to-earn-gold/|title=Tips to Earn Gold|website=Arena of Valor (AoV) Wiki Guide|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-03}}</ref> In addition to this, players can play a 'Ranked' match type, which allows them to attempt to go up in tiers in order to be matched with players who are at their skill level.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://samurai-gamers.com/arena-of-valor/ranked-match/|title=Arena of Valor (AoV) - Ranked Match (Game Modes)|last=Green|date=2017-11-18|website=SAMURAI GAMERS|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-03}}</ref> Stars are earnt for a victory, and lost when the player loses.\n\nThere are various game modes, with 5v5, also known as Grand Battle or Ranked, being the most popular. Here, players can choose a role to play in, such as marksmen, who do high damage yet have little health, or a tank, which has a lot of health. The team then coordinate in order to destroy the towers, and finally to destroy the enemy base. Players can choose to play in the 'jungle', which allows them to level up quicker and make a large difference to the game. \n\nIn addition to this, Valley Skirmish is a 3v3 game mode, using a much smaller map. In this version of the game, there is only one tower. These games are designed to be much quicker, for the player that does not have time for a longer game, and typically last for 4 - 6 minutes. Abyssal Clash is a game mode where players are randomly selected heroes, and have two towers they must destroy in order to reach the enemy base. Arena of Valor also has a Deathmatch mode, however this is not as popular as the other three modes.\n\n=== Hero types ===\nThere are currently 98 heroes in ''Arena of Valor'' as of April 6, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.arenaofvalor.com/|title=Arena of Valor Hero List|website=Arena of Valor|language=en|access-date=2019-02-03}}</ref> ''Arena of Valor'' divides the heroes into numerous categories that each play different roles.  The most notable difference is the type of damage a hero deals - some heroes deal physical damage, which can be countered by the armor stat, whilst other heroes deal mainly magic damage, which is resisted by the magic resistance stat. However, some heroes deal both types of damage, and some heroes deal 'true' damage, which cannot be countered by either the armor or magic resistance stat. All heroes are classified as one of six categories, however some heroes can overlap and go into more than one category. \n\n* Marksman: Also known as \"AD Carry/ADC\", marksmen are ranged heroes that usually deal physical damage mostly through their auto attack. This hero type often deals sustained damage, and therefore are useful in teamfights in order to reduce the health of the opponent. In addition to this, they are useful in taking down objectives in order to win the game. However, they do not have much health and therefore are very fragile and vulnerable. Examples of marksmen are Tel'Annas, Valhein, and Yorn.\n* Mage: Mages are sometimes known as \"AP Carry/APC\". These heroes deal lots of burst magic damage. Some mages tend to be fragile, while some mages tend to be more durable, depends on respective itemization. Mages are a mix of ranged heroes, which deal high amounts of burst damage from afar, or melee heroes, which deal lots of damage from close up, or a mixture of both.  Examples of mages are Lauriel, Liliana, and Tulen.\n* Assassin: These are heroes that are designed to deal large amounts of damage quickly, and often do not have much health. This hero type often searches for the marksman or mage from the enemy team, as well as any other fragile heroes, and also being responsible to shut down any enemy unit that is on a killing spree. They have high mobility and burst damage in order to be able to strike at valuable targets on the oppositions team. Examples of assassins are Murad, Nakroth, and Zill.\n* [[Tank (gaming)|Tank]]: Tanks are heroes that have large amounts of HP, and usually built completely defensive to be able to take damage for the team.  As a result, they often deal little damage. However, they often have abilities known as 'crowd control' that allow them to inhibit the movement of the enemy team. In addition to this, they can use these abilities to initiate a teamfight, or to prevent the enemy team from attacking high priority targets such as ally marksman or mage. Examples of tanks are Xeniel, Thane, and Toro.\n* Warrior:  Heroes that blend the attributes of damage dealer and tank, combining moderate survivability with respectable damage. Warriors usually have balanced amount of health, defenses, and attack damage, which is common designation for close-range melee duelist. Thus, they able to survive in a long period of fight and excel in doing continuos sustain damage. This type of heroes are also great against all odds, and tend to be extremely strong in 1v1 scenario. Examples of warriors are Florentino, Rourke, and Omen.\n* Support: Heroes whose abilities aid the rest of the team by providing healing, buffing allies (such as movement speed buffs), debuffing the enemy team (such as stunning), or a combination of the above. Support heroes are often paired with the marksman in the early laning phase of the game where the support doesn't require to kill minions, but instead focuses on aiding their partner and harassing the enemy heroes. Support heroes usually aids ally marksman as they are often weaker during the early phase of the game and need assistance in order to survive. Example of supports are Alice, Annette, and Krizzix.\n\nPlayers can purchase items, which make a large impact on the hero stats and playstyle. An example of this is Zephys, a dual warrior/assassin class. He have a passive ability that make him increase damage reduction against incoming damage to him based on the percentage of the amount of health loss. If only offensive items are bought, he will deal a lot of damage but has low amount of health and defenses, and may not survive for long. If Zephys purchase a mix of offensive and defensive items, he can soak damage for the team while he still be able to deal noticable amount of damage. If Zephys buy only defensive items, he can boost his damage reduction passive to its maximum potential, being literally almost impossible to die in most circumstances, but he will deal drastically low amount of damage.\n\nThis kind of playstyle can be applied to all heroes, allowing tanks to act as warriors, or for mages to act as supports, and vice versa.\n\n== History and development ==\n''Arena of Valor'' (formerly ''Strike of Kings'') is an international adaptation of ''[[Wangzhe Rongyao|Honor of Kings]]'' for markets outside mainland China. In 2015, Tencent approached [[Riot Games]] and asked them to turn their popular [[multiplayer online battle arena]] (MOBA) game ''[[League of Legends]]'' into a mobile title. However, Riot Games declined and claimed that the gameplay of ''League of Legends'' could not be replicated on smartphones. Tencent then proceeded to create their own mobile MOBA game, ''[[Wangzhe Rongyao]]'', roughly translated to English as ''Honor of Kings'', and was released in November 26, 2015. Nevertheless, several Riot Games employees deemed that the design of characters and abilities in ''Honor of Kings'' were \"blatantly ripping off the intellectual property of ''League of Legends''\", and reportedly brought these concerns to Tencent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.techinasia.com/chinas-top-mobile-game-complete-league-legends-ripoff|title=China top mobile game  is a complete League of Legends ripoff|last=Custer|first=Christopher|date=July 27, 2016|website=Tech in Asia|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Tencent then responded that they would changing its own game enough to sell as a standalone product with no relation to ''League of Legends''. Despite this, ''Honor of Kings'' already gained massive popularity in China at this point. Tencent felt its too late to make huge changes to the game, so Tencent decided that ''Honor of Kings'' will only go through small necessary changes while the international release of the game outside mainland China will be the one that featuring different contents, hence leading to the creation of ''Arena of Valor''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dotesports.com/league-of-legends/news/riot-strained-relationship-tencent-declining-players-mobile-games-information-32079|title=Riot\u2019s relationship with Tencent has reportedly been strained over declining profits and mobile games|last=Mickunas |first=Aaron |website=dotesports|access-date=2018-08-21}}</ref> \n\n''Arena of Valor'' is developed by [[TiMi Studios]] with the same engine and UI design as ''Honor of Kings'' and published by [[Tencent Games]] for western marketing, with [[Garena]] joined the development as they helped to westernize the atmosphere of the game. The in-game characters have been swapped from characters inspired by [[Chinese folklore]] [[Chinese mythology|and mythology]], to characters inspired by [[European folklore]] and some [[mythology|mythologies from other nations]] with blend a variety of elements including [[Lovecraftian horror]], [[steampunk]], [[high fantasy]], and [[sword and sorcery]] to appeal audiences outside mainland China, with the appearance of in-game characters mostly recycled but with fresh revamped designs of characters from ''[[Heroes of Newerth]]'', a MOBA game that Garena had acquired from [[S2 Games]]. Thus, this made ''Arena of Valor'' a [[spiritual successor]] to ''Heroes of Newerth''. \n\n''Arena of Valor'' also included several characters such as Butterfly, Violet, and Mina from ''Age of Gunslingers'' ({{zh|s=\u69cd\u795e\u7d00|c=|t=|p=Qi\u00e1ngsh\u00e9nj\u00ec}}), a [[Third-person shooter]] (TPS) game that was also developed by Tencent and TiMi Studios. In spite of that, the aforementioned characters have different lore than the game they originally hailed from.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/AgeOfGunslingersOnline|title=Age of Gunslingers|last=|first=|date=March 8, 2018|website=TVTropes|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://baike.baidu.com/item/%E6%9E%AA%E7%A5%9E%E7%BA%AA/6657145|title=Age of Gunslingers (\u67aa\u795e\u7eaa)|last=|first=|date=March 21, 2012|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=wuTa3XbRgZU&t=24s|title=\u5200\u92d2\u5bf6\u8c9d\u3001\u7f8e\u5a1c \u300a\u69cd\u795e\u7d00\u300b\u52d5\u756bPV\u3001\u89d2\u8272\u4ecb\u7d39\u4e32\u71d2\uff01\uff01Strike of Kings\uff08\u50b3\u8aaa\u5c0d\u8a23x\u69cd\u795e\u7d00)|last=|first=|date=March 3, 2017|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Additionally, ''Arena of Valor'' had multiple collaboration with other franchises, including having [[Crossover (fiction)|crossovers]] with [[DC Universe]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bluemoongame.com/what-are-dc-characters-doing-in-arena-of-valor/|title=What are DC characters doing in Arena of Valor?|last=|first=|date=November 15, 2017|website=Blue Moon Game|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://comicbook.com/gaming/amp/2018/04/19/tencent-interview-superman-arena-of-valor-mobile-80th-anniversary/|title=Exclusive Interview: Tencent Talks Superman\u2019s Debut In Arena of Valor, In Time For His 80th Anniversary.|last=|first=|date=April 18, 2018|website=comicbook.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://criticalindex.net/arena-of-valor-completes-dc-character-line-up-flash-joins-the-battle-b992e5fb814e|title=Arena of Valor completes DC characters line up|last=|first=|date=August 5, 2018|website=criticalindex.net|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> and ''Wiro Sableng'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://id.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wiro_Sableng|title=Wikipedia (Indonesian language) - Wiro Sableng|last=|first=|date=December 21, 2006|website=Wikipedia|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://esports.id/arena-of-valor/news/2018/07/1baff70e2669e8376347efd3a874a341/wujudkan-nuansa-lokal-wiro-sableng-hadir-di-arena-of-valor|title=Wujudkan nuansa lokal,Wiro Sableng hadir di Arena of Valor|last=|first=|date=July 27, 2018|website=Esports ID|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/life/2018/10/14/wiro-sableng-game-now-available-on-taiwan-aov-servers.html|title=Wiro Sableng now available in Taiwan server|last=|first=|date=October 14, 2018|website=The Jakarta Post|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://samurai-gamers.com/arena-of-valor/who-is-wiro-sableng/|title=Who is Wiro Sableng?|last=|first=|date=September 11, 2018|website=Samurai Gamers|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> and collaborated with [[KFC]] to advertising the game, notably in Taiwan and Thailand,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pocketgamer.biz/asia/news/72538/arena-of-valor-kfc-colonel-sanders-deal/|title=Arena of Valor confirmed having partnership with KFC.|last=|first=|date=March 6, 2020|website=Pocket Gamer|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> with [[Colonel Sanders]] made his appearance in the game as a skin for Ormarr.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oneesports.gg/aov/kfcs-colonel-sanders-is-now-a-playable-character-in-arena-of-valor/|title=KFC's Colonel Sanders made his appearance in Arena of Valor|last=|first=|date=February 13, 2020|website=ONE Esports|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nOriginally, Tencent actually intended to feature [[Marvel Comics]]'s characters during the earliest development stage of the game before they collaborated with [[DC Comics]], and has Close Beta Test (CBT) of the game under the name of ''Marvel Super Heroes MOBA'' ({{zh|s=\u8d85\u7ea7\u6218\u573a|c=|t=|p=Ch\u0101oj\u00ed zh\u00e0nch\u01ceng}}). The game feature some characters from Tencent's IP such as Butterfly, Violet, Mina, Valhein, and Zanis having crossover with Marvel's characters.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=R3QAbaznQFI|title=[CLOSED] Heroes Spotlight {{!}} Marvel Super Heroes MOBA \u8d85\u7ea7\u6218\u573a|last=#VKMOBA|first=V.K|date=September 30, 2016|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> However, Marvel then took back their license, and Tencent had to shut down the game and restart the development from scratch, in which also resulted TiMi Studios have to redesign the game in which made how ''Arena of Valor'' currently looks like. Tencent then approached DC Comics for collaboration to include DC's characters as replacement.\n\nThe soundtrack for ''Arena of Valor'' is composed by American music artist Matthew Carl Earl, proving a different atmosphere compared to the original score with Chinese music instruments in ''Honor of Kings''.\n\n''Arena of Valor'' have wide variety of publishers for different regions. ''Arena of Valor'' was first launched in Taiwan on October 14, 2016 by Garena, following a two-week closed beta testing period.<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://www.4gamers.com.tw/news/detail/30437/garena-new-mobile-moba-game | title = Garena\u300a\u50b3\u8aaa\u5c0d\u6c7a\u300b\u63ed\u958b\u795e\u79d8\u9762\u7d17\uff0c\u5c01\u6e2c\u9810\u767b\u6d3b\u52d5\u5373\u65e5\u958b\u8dd1 | author = 4Gamers | language = Chinese | accessdate = January 5, 2018 | website = 4Gamers \u5b98\u65b9\u7db2\u7ad9}}</ref> On October 17, 2017, Garena launched ''Arena of Valor'' in Malaysia, Singapore, and Philippines, where majority of the gaming community are playing mobile games. Garena decided to combined these three countries in one server. In South Korea, the game was published by [[Netmarble]] on April 26, 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mmoculture.com/2017/03/penta-storm-netmarble-prepares-to-launch-its-first-mobile-moba-in-korea/|title=Netmarble preparing to launch Strike of Kings as Penta Storm in Korea|last=|first=|date=March 10, 2017|website=MMO Culture|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The game was released in European app stores by Tencent in August 10, 2017,<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://forum.sok.proximabeta.com/forum.php?mod=viewthread&tid=1124 | title = A Big Update is Coming: A Letter From the Producer \u2013 Game Updates \u2013  Arena of Valor Forum | author = Joseph | date = July 25, 2017 | accessdate = January 5, 2018 | work = Arena of Valor Forum | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180105233730/https://forum.sok.proximabeta.com/forum.php?mod=viewthread&tid=1124 | archive-date = January 5, 2018 | url-status = dead | df = mdy-all }}</ref> and was released in North and Latin American mobile app stores on December 19, 2017.<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://www.theverge.com/2017/12/18/16469736/tencent-arena-of-valor-honor-of-King-north-america-launch | title = Tencent is bringing China's biggest game to the rest of the world | first = Andrew | last= Webster | date = December 18, 2017 | accessdate = December 18, 2017 | work = [[The Verge]]}}</ref> On June 28, 2018, Tencent implemented \"Asia server\" unannounced. The server included Australia, New Zealand, Myanmar, Laos, Cambodia, and Brunei. In Japan, [[DeNA]] cooperated with Tencent to launch ''Arena of Valor'' on November 30, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://samurai-gamers.com/arena-of-valor/japan-preregistration-begins/|title=AoV Japan server pre-registration|last=|first=|date=November 6, 2018|website=Samurai Gamers|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nThe game was announced to be released for the [[Nintendo Switch]] console during the September 2017 [[List of Nintendo Direct presentations|Nintendo Direct presentation]].<ref name=\"NL cites Switch announcement\">{{cite web |url=http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2017/09/free-to-play_moba_arena_of_valor_is_fighting_towards_switch |date=September 14, 2017 |accessdate=August 21, 2018 |last=McFerran |first=Damien |website=[[Nintendo Life]] |title=Free-To-Play MOBA Arena Of Valor Is Fighting Towards Switch}}</ref> A closed beta became available for the platform between June and July 2018,<ref name=\"BlueMoonGame Switch beta announced\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bluemoongame.com/arena-of-valor-gets-to-switch-in-beta-now-and-a-new-hero-2/|title=Arena Of Valor Gets To Switch, In Beta Now, And A New Hero|last=Jevtic|first=Stevan|date=June 19, 2018|website=Blue Moon Game|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=June 19, 2018}}</ref> and participants received an exclusive in-game skin for one of the characters.<ref name=\"NL cites Switch beta\">{{cite web |url=http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2018/06/arena_of_valor_closed_beta_starts_on_28th_june_participants_receive_exclusive_in-game_skin |date=June 23, 2018 |accessdate=August 21, 2018 |last=Doolan |first=Liam |website=[[Nintendo Life]] |title=Arena Of Valor Closed Beta Starts On 28th June, Participants Receive Exclusive In-Game Skin}}</ref> The game is confirmed to launch on the platform in September 25, 2018.<ref name=\"NL cites Switch launch\">{{cite web |url=http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2018/08/free-to-play_moba_arena_of_valor_launches_on_switch_this_september |date=August 21, 2018 |accessdate=August 21, 2018 |last=Doolan |first=Liam |website=[[Nintendo Life]] |title=Free-To-Play MOBA Arena Of Valor Launches On Switch This September}}</ref>\n\nSpeaking to [[Engadget]], Tencent Games revealed the Nintendo Switch port of the game is enhanced and optimized for the platform, taking advantage of the console's processing power and hardware features to implement various changes to the game, such as improved graphics and animations, better lighting, smoother lines, and additional minute details like butterflies. Additionally, several adjustments were made to the game to be playable on a bigger screen with traditional controls, and characters' stats have been reconfigured. Because of these changes, cross-play between the Nintendo Switch and mobile versions of the game is not possible. Tencent Games also have plans for competitive events based on the Nintendo Switch version.<ref name=\"Engadget interview\">{{cite web |url=https://www.engadget.com/2018/08/23/arena-of-valor-switch-interview-esports/ |date=August 23, 2018 |accessdate=August 27, 2018 |last=Conditt |first=Jessica |publisher=[[Engadget]] |title='Arena of Valor' is a completely different game on Switch}}</ref>\n\nRiot Games implied that their relationship with Tencent is still strong, and the conflict between them and their games is simply just \"a bump in the road\". In 2017, Riot Games filed a lawsuit against [[Moonton]], the developer of the mobile game ''[[Mobile Legends: Bang Bang]]'', because of copyright infringement, citing similarities between ''Mobile Legends'' and ''League of Legends''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://straatosphere.com/riot-games-sues-mobile-legends-developer/amp/|title=Riot Games sues League of Legends copycat|last=|first=|date=July 11, 2017|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.akshonesports.com/article/2017/07/riot-games-suing-shanghai-moonton-technology-copyright-infringement|title=Riot Games suing Moonton for copyright infringement|last=|first=|date=July 11, 2017|website=Akshon Esports|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The case was initially dismissed in Central District Court of California in United States on account of ''[[forum non conveniens]]''. Tencent, as Riot's parent company, on behalf of Riot Games, then filed a new, separate lawsuit directly targeting Moonton's CEO, Watson Xu Zhenhua in a Chinese court, which ruled in Tencent's favor in July 2018, awarded Tencent {{US$|2.9&nbsp;million|long=no}} ([[Renminbi|RMB]]19.4 million) in term of damages.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://dotesports.com/league-of-legends/news/source-riot-games-parent-tencent-wins-lawsuit-mobile-legends-31079 |title=Riot Games parent Tencent wins $2.9 million in lawsuit against Moonton CEO |first=Aaron |last=Mickunas |date=July 18, 2018 |website=[[Dot Esports]] |access-date=November 24, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190711104720/https://dotesports.com/league-of-legends/news/source-riot-games-parent-tencent-wins-lawsuit-mobile-legends-31079 |archive-date=July 11, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/gaming/news/riot-games-tencent-wins-lawsuit-league-of-legends-copy-1202878322/ |title=Tencent Wins Lawsuit Over 'League of Legends' Copycat |first=Liz |last=Lanier |date=July 19, 2018 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |access-date=November 24, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330075502/https://variety.com/2018/gaming/news/riot-games-tencent-wins-lawsuit-league-of-legends-copy-1202878322/ |archive-date=March 30, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> In addition, with both ''Honor of Kings'' and ''Arena of Valor'' still continuosly increasing popularity, playerbase, and have huge esports scene, Riot Games then realized and acknowledged the potential of mobile market for MOBA genre. Riot Games eventually announced their own mobile MOBA game, ''[[League of Legends: Wild Rift]]'' on October 16, 2019, which is 10th year anniversary of ''League of Legends''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/platform/amp/2019/10/15/20915315/league-of-legends-wild-rift-mobile-console-launch|title=League of Legends coming to mobile & console|last=|first=|date=October 15, 2019|website=The Verge|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Esports==\n===International competition===\n''Arena of Valor'' tournaments have been held in numerous regions, and each regions have their own local leagues such as Garena Challenger Series Pro League (GCS) in Taiwan,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=PEygJPtP4lM|title=AoV GCS Summer 2017 Highlights|last=|first=|date=October 11, 2017|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://liquipedia.net/arenaofvalor/Garena_Challenger_Series/2020/Spring|title=Garena Challenger Series Spring 2020|last=|first=|date=February 15, 2020|website=Liquipedia.net|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Realm of Valor Pro League (RPL) in Thailand,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=PEygJPtP4lM|title=Realm of Valor Pro League Summer 2020|last=|first=|date=January 31, 2020|website=Liquipedia.net|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Arena of Glory (AOG) in Vietnam,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://liquipedia.net/arenaofvalor/Arena_of_Glory/2019/Spring|title=Arena of Glory Spring 2019|last=|first=|date=February 23, 2019|website=Liquipedia.net|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Arena of Valor Star League (ASL) in Indonesia,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://liquipedia.net/arenaofvalor/AOV_Star_League/Season_4|title=Arena of Valor Star League Season 4|last=|first=|date=April 27, 2020|website=Liquipedia.net|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Arena of Valor: Valor Cup (AVC) in Malaysia, Singapore and Philippines,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://samurai-gamers.com/arena-of-valor/malaysia-first-aov-valor-cup-details/|title=AoV First Valor Cup details.|last=|first=|date=March 2, 2018|website=Samurai Gamers|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Arena of Valor: Valor Series (AVS) in Europe, North America, and Latin America,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.invenglobal.com/articles/7459/tencents-valor-series-season-3-starts-this-weekend-in-arena-of-valor-tournament-structure-detailed|title=Arena of Valor: Valor Series  Season 3|last=|first=|date=February 1, 2019|website=INVEN Global|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> and Arena of Valor Japan League (AJL) in Japan.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://liquipedia.net/arenaofvalor/Arena_of_Valor_Japan_League/2020/Spring|title=Arena of Valor Japan League Spring 2020|last=|first=|date=March 7, 2020|website=Liquipedia.net|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=u0LPcJu5Y5U&t=28s|title=\u3010 \u4f1d\u8aac\u5bfe\u6c7a -Arena of Valor-\u3011Arena of Valor Japan League \u6625\u306e\u9663 \u6c7a\u52dd\u6226|last=|first=|date=March 28, 2020|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n''Arena of Valor'' also have world championship tournament under the name of Arena of Valor International Championship (AIC) and Arena of Valor World Cup (AWC). Both are annual tournament. The difference between the two is AIC is a tournament that teams from across the world participate to earn profit and glory for their own team, while AWC is a tournament that teams from across the world participate to represent their own country.\n\nArena of Valor International Championship (AIC) that was first held in 2017, the event attracted more than 36,000,000 online viewers, breaking mobile game records worldwide and has since became the leading standard of mobile eSports. The game occupying the top positions of mobile game rankings in Asia for months has also received the honor of Google Play\u2019s Best of 2017 Game award in Europe.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamerbraves.com/arena-of-valor-brings-world-cup-2018-to-los-angeles/|title=Arena of Valor International Championship (AIC) that was first held in 2017, the event attracted more than 36,000,000 online viewers, breaking mobile game records worldwide and has since became the leading standard of mobile eSports.|last=|first=|date=April 22, 2017|website=Gamer Braves|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The second AIC tournament, was held in Thailand, from November 23, 2018 till December 16, 2018. The competiton featured more teams than the first year, increased to 16 teams from different regions to battle it out, competing for the title and a portion prize pool of $600,000 (\u00a3460,000).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://esportsinsider.com/2018/10/arena-of-valor-announces-international-championship/|title=Arena of Valor announces international championship|last=|first=|date=October 19, 2018|website=Esports Insider|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> \n\nThe first Arena of Valor World Cup (AWC) tournament was held in Los Angeles, United States, from July 17, 2018 till July 28, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamerbraves.com/arena-of-valor-brings-world-cup-2018-to-los-angeles/|title=Arena of Valor brings World Cup 2018 to Los Angeles|last=|first=|date=May 26, 2018|website=GamerBraves|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> A total prize pool of $500,000 made AWC as one of the largest-scale mobile eSports tournaments in gaming history. A total of nine regions competed for the grand prize which includes Taiwan - Hong Kong - Macau, Thailand, Vietnam, Malaysia - Singapore - Philippines, Indonesia, South Korea, North America, Latin America and Europe. Additionally, the tournament host selected three Wildcard teams to participate in AWC.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://liquipedia.net/arenaofvalor/Arena_of_Valor_World_Cup/2018|title=Arena of Valor World Cup 2018|last=|first=|date=July 17, 2018|website=Liquipedia|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The second AWC tournament, was held in Danang, Vietnam, from June 27, 2019 till July 14, 2019, with the same total prize pool of $500,000 just like the first AWC.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://esportsobserver.com/aov-2019-world-cup-vietnam/|title=AoV 2019 World Cup will be held in Vietnam|last=|first=|date=February 27, 2019|website=The Esports Observer|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://egg.network/news/arena-valor-world-cup-2019-will-be-hosted-vietnam-usd500000-prize-pool|title=AWC 2019 will be hosted in Vietnam with US$500,000 prize pool|last=|first=|date=May 13, 2019|website=egg.network|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The second AWC also marks Japan\u2019s first participation in an ''AOV'' international tournament since the game introduced their Japanese server in November 30, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gameishard.gg/aov/arena-of-valor-world-cup-2019-announces-12-teams-to-compete-for-usd-500000-prize-pool/amp/|title=Arena of Valor World Cup 2019|last=|first=|date=April 24, 2019|website=Game Is Hard|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dotesports.com/mobile/news/vietnam-wins-the-arena-of-valor-world-cup-2019/|title=Vietnam wins the Arena of Valor World Cup 2019|last=|first=|date=July 15, 2019|website=dotesports.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n===Asian Games 2018===\n{{Main|Arena of Valor at the 2018 Asian Games}}\n\n''Arena of Valor'' are part of electronic sports demonstration event in [[Asian Games]] 2018 held in Indonesia. Eight countries are able to participate after qualified from their respective regional qualification with Indonesia automatically qualifies as host. Unlike other electronic sports event, there is no qualification for Central and West Asia.<ref>{{cite news |title=AESF Game Result |url=https://www.aesf.com/images/Game_Result.pdf |accessdate=11 July 2018 |publisher=Asian Electronic Sports Federation |date=11 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180831012203/https://www.aesf.com/images/Game_Result.pdf |archive-date=2018-08-31 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n===Southeast Asian Games 2019===\n{{Main|Esports at the 2019 Southeast Asian Games}}\n\n''Arena of Valor'' is among the games title to be included as a medal event at the [[2019 Southeast Asian Games]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.insidethegames.biz/articles/1077291/arena-of-valor-to-become-official-game-title-of-2019-southeast-asian-games-in-philippines|title=Arena of Valor become official game title of 2019 Southeast Asian Games in Philippines.|last=|first=|date=March 27, 2019|website=insidethegames.biz|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\n''Arena of Valor'' won the award for \"Best Music in a Casual/Social Game\" at the 15th Annual Game Audio Network Guild Awards, whereas its other nomination was for \"Best Original Instrumental\".<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.audiogang.org/awards/2017-awards/ | title = 2017 Awards | accessdate = April 16, 2018 | work = Game Audio Network Guild}}</ref> It was also nominated for \"Original Score \u2013 Video Game\" at the 2017 [[Hollywood Music in Media Awards]],<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/hollywood-music-media-awards-full-winners-list-1057748/item/original-score-tv-show-limited-series-1057712 | title = Hollywood Music in Media Awards: Full Winners List | date = November 17, 2017 | accessdate = March 14, 2018 | work = [[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref> for \"Original Dramatic Score, New IP\" at the [[NAVGTR Awards]],<ref>{{cite web | url = https://navgtr.org/2018/03/13/horizon-wins-7-mario-goty/ | title = Winner List for 2017: Mario, Horizon | date = March 13, 2018 | accessdate = November 6, 2019 | work = [[NAVGTR Awards|National Academy of Video Game Trade Reviewers]]}}</ref> for \"Best Competitive Game\" at the 2018 [[Golden Joystick Awards]],<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/gaming/news/golden-joysticks-2018-nominees-announced-voting-open-now/ | title = Golden Joysticks 2018 nominees announced, voting open now | first = Tom | last = Hoggins | date = September 24, 2018 | accessdate = October 7, 2018 | newspaper = [[The Daily Telegraph]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.gamesradar.com/golden-joystick-awards-2018-winners/ | title = Golden Joystick Awards 2018 winners: God of War wins big but Fortnite gets Victory Royale | first = Connor | last = Sheridan | date = November 16, 2018 | accessdate = November 17, 2018 | work = [[GamesRadar+]]}}</ref> and for \"Fan Favorite Mobile Game\" at the [[Gamers' Choice Awards]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://file770.com/2018-gamers-choice-awards-nominees/ | title = 2018 Gamers' Choice Awards Nominees | first = Mike | last = Glyer | date = November 19, 2018 | accessdate = January 15, 2019 | work = File 770}}</ref> ''Arena of Valor: Flip the World'' won the award for \"Song/Score - Mobile Video Game\" at the [[9th Hollywood Music in Media Awards]],<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.hmmawards.com/2018-hmma-winners/ | title = 2018 HMMA WINNERS | date = November 14, 2018 | accessdate = November 15, 2018 | work = [[Hollywood Music in Media Awards]]}}</ref> while the game itself and ''Honor of Kings 2.0'' were nominated for the same category at the 10th Hollywood Music in Media Awards.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.shootonline.com/spw/hollywood-music-media-awards-announces-nominees | title = Hollywood Music In Media Awards Announces Nominees | date = November 4, 2019 | accessdate = November 6, 2019 | work = [[Shoot (advertising magazine)|Shoot]]}}</ref> The game was also nominated for \"Best Mobile Sport\" at the ''[[Pocket Gamer]]'' Mobile Games Awards,<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.mobilegamesawards.com/winners-2020/ | title = The winners of 2020 | accessdate = January 30, 2020 | work = [[Pocket Gamer]]}}</ref> while ''Honor of Kings 2.0'' was nominated for \"Best Sound Design in a Causal/Social Game\" and \"Best Music in a Casual Game\" at the 18th Annual Game Audio Network Guild Awards;<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.thehypemagazine.com/2020/02/game-audio-network-guild-announces-18th-annual-g-a-n-g-award-nominees/ | title = Game Audio Network Guild Announces 18th Annual G.A.N.G. Award Nominees | first = Kelly | last = Wilson | date = February 13, 2020 | accessdate = February 27, 2020 | work = The Hype Magazine}}</ref> however, the latter event was postponed to a later date due to concerns over the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/gdc-postponed-coronavirus-concerns-1281672 | title = Game Developers Conference \"Postponed\" Amid Coronavirus Concerns  |first = Patrick | last = Shanley | date = February 28, 2020 | accessdate = February 29, 2020 | work = [[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{notelist}}\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|https://www.arenaofvalor.com/}}\n\n{{Tencent Holdings}}\n\n[[Category:2017 video games]]\n[[Category:Android (operating system) games]]\n[[Category:IOS games]]\n[[Category:Multiplayer online battle arena games]]\n[[Category:Nintendo Switch eShop games]]\n[[Category:Tencent]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in China]]\n[[Category:Video games based on DC Comics]]\n[[Category:Unity (game engine) games]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox video game\n| title = Arena of Valor\n| image = Arena of Valor logo.png\n| developer = [[Tencent]], [[TiMi Studios]], [[Garena]]\n| publisher = [[Tencent]] (Europe, North America, Latin America, Australasia, Middle East - North Africa, South Asia, Russia)\n\n[[Garena]] (Taiwan, Macau, Hong Kong, & Southeast Asia)\n\n[[Netmarble]] (South Korea)\n\n[[DeNA]] (Japan)\n\nSixjoy (India) (Formerly)\nProxima Beta (Europe) (Formerly)\n| composer = {{ubl|Jeff Broadbent|Matthew Carl Earl|[[Hans Zimmer]]}}\n| platforms = [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[iOS]], [[Nintendo Switch]]\n| released = '''Android, iOS'''{{Video game release|[[China|CHN]]|November 26, 2015 ([[Honor of Kings|HoK]])|[[Taiwan|TWN]]|October 14, 2016|[[Vietnam|VN]]|November 21, 2016|[[Thailand|TH]]|December 26, 2016|[[South Korea|KR]]|April 26, 2017|[[Indonesia|IDN]]|June 6, 2017|EU|August 10, 2017|[[Malaysia|MY]], [[Singapore|SG]], & [[Philippines|PH]]|October 17, 2017|[[NA]] & [[Latin America|LATAM]]|December 19, 2017|[[India|IND]]|March 1, 2018|[[Australasia|AU]], [[Brunei|BRU]], [[Myanmar|MMR]], [[Laos|LA]], & [[Cambodia|CBD]]|June 28, 2018|[[Japan|JPN]]|November 30, 2018|[[MENA]], [[South Asia|SA]], & [[Russia|RU]]|April 16, 2020}}\n\n\n'''Nintendo Switch''' {{Video game release|WW|September 25, 2018}}\n| display = ''' Alternative Name On Various Servers'''{{ubl|Thailand Server - ''Realm of Valor''/''RoV'' (First official English name, but this server still use it till today)|Indonesian Server - ''Mobile Arena'' (Formerly before renamed to ''Arena of Valor'')|Europe Server - ''Strike of Kings'' (Formerly before renamed to ''Arena of Valor'')|Vietnam Server - ''Li\u00ean Qu\u00e2n'' (Roughly translated to ''Arena of Valor'' in [[English language|English]])|Korean Server - ''Penta Storm''/\ud39c\ud0c0\uc2a4\ud1b0 (''Penta Seutom'')|Taiwan Server - ''Legendary Showdown''/\u50b3\u8aaa\u5c0d\u6c7a (''Chu\u00e1nshu\u014d Du\u00ecju\u00e9'')|Japan Server - ''Legendary Showdown''/\u4f1d\u8aac\u5bfe\u6c7a (''Densetsu Taiketsu'')}}\n| genre = [[Multiplayer online battle arena]]\n| modes = [[Multiplayer]]\n}}\n\n'''''Arena of Valor''''' ('''''AoV''''') ({{zh|s=\u50b3\u8aaa\u5c0d\u6c7a|p=Chu\u00e1nshu\u014d Du\u00ecju\u00e9}}), formerly '''''Realm of Valor''''' then '''''Strike of Kings''''', is an international adaptation of ''[[Wangzhe Rongyao|Honor of Kings]]'' ({{zh|s=\u738b\u8005\u8363\u8000|p=W\u00e1ngzh\u011b R\u00f3ngy\u00e0o}}), also known in English unofficial translations as '''''Kings of Glory''''', a [[multiplayer online battle arena]] developed by [[TiMi Studios]] and published by [[Tencent Games]] for [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[iOS]] and [[Nintendo Switch]] for markets outside mainland China. As of September 2018, the game has grossed over {{US$|140 million|long=no}} outside China.<ref>{{cite news |last=Spannbauer |first=Adam |title=Arena of Valor Revenue Clears $140 Million Outside China |url=https://sensortower.com/blog/arena-of-valor-revenue-outside-china |work=Sensor Tower |date=September 17, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Gameplay ==\n''Arena of Valor'' is a [[3D computer graphics|3D]], [[Third-person (video games)|third-person]], [[multiplayer online battle arena]] (MOBA) style game for mobile. The game has multiple modes, with the main three being Grand Battle, Valley Skirmish and Abyssal Clash.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://samurai-gamers.com/arena-of-valor/game-modes-overview/|title=Arena of Valor (AoV) - Game Modes Overview (Abyssal Clash, Hook Wars, etc.)|last=Green|date=2018-02-20|website=SAMURAI GAMERS|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-03}}</ref> Players compete in these matches which on average last for around 12 - 18 minutes. Players aim to destroy turrets on the map, in order to destroy the core.\n\nThe overall gameplay of ''Arena of Valor'' highly resembles a game called ''[[League of Legends]]'', a MOBA game developed and published by [[Riot Games]], which is a subsidiary of Tencent.\n\nPlayers control characters, referred to as heroes, and each of these heroes have a unique set of abilities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.arenaofvalor.com/|title=Arena of Valor|website=Arena of Valor|language=en|access-date=2019-02-03}}</ref> Heroes start the game at a low level, and can earn level up in various ways. Killing non-player creatures such as minions or monsters, defeating other players, destroying structures, passively through time and through special items that can be purchased through the shop. These actions also increase XP the player has, making them more powerful. The items purchased do not carry over matches, and therefore all players are on equal footing at the start of the match.\n\nMatches give players rewards, such as gold, which can then be used to buy a variety of heroes, or arcana.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mobilegamerhub.com/arena-of-valor/tips-to-earn-gold/|title=Tips to Earn Gold|website=Arena of Valor (AoV) Wiki Guide|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-03}}</ref> In addition to this, players can play a 'Ranked' match type, which allows them to attempt to go up in tiers in order to be matched with players who are at their skill level.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://samurai-gamers.com/arena-of-valor/ranked-match/|title=Arena of Valor (AoV) - Ranked Match (Game Modes)|last=Green|date=2017-11-18|website=SAMURAI GAMERS|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-03}}</ref> Stars are earnt for a victory, and lost when the player loses.\n\nThere are various game modes, with 5v5, also known as Grand Battle or Ranked, being the most popular. Here, players can choose a role to play in, such as marksmen, who do high damage yet have little health, or a tank, which has a lot of health. The team then coordinate in order to destroy the towers, and finally to destroy the enemy base. Players can choose to play in the 'jungle', which allows them to level up quicker and make a large difference to the game. \n\nIn addition to this, Valley Skirmish is a 3v3 game mode, using a much smaller map. In this version of the game, there is only one tower. These games are designed to be much quicker, for the player that does not have time for a longer game, and typically last for 4 - 6 minutes. Abyssal Clash is a game mode where players are randomly selected heroes, and have two towers they must destroy in order to reach the enemy base. Arena of Valor also has a Deathmatch mode, however this is not as popular as the other three modes.\n\n=== Hero types ===\nThere are currently 98 heroes in ''Arena of Valor'' as of April 6, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.arenaofvalor.com/|title=Arena of Valor Hero List|website=Arena of Valor|language=en|access-date=2019-02-03}}</ref> ''Arena of Valor'' divides the heroes into numerous categories that each play different roles.  The most notable difference is the type of damage a hero deals - some heroes deal physical damage, which can be countered by the armor stat, whilst other heroes deal mainly magic damage, which is resisted by the magic resistance stat. However, some heroes deal both types of damage, and some heroes deal 'true' damage, which cannot be countered by either the armor or magic resistance stat. All heroes are classified as one of six categories, however some heroes can overlap and go into more than one category. \n\n* Marksman: Also known as \"AD Carry/ADC\", marksmen are ranged heroes that usually deal physical damage mostly through their auto attack. This hero type often deals sustained damage, and therefore are useful in teamfights in order to reduce the health of the opponent. In addition to this, they are useful in taking down objectives in order to win the game. However, they do not have much health and therefore are very fragile and vulnerable. Examples of marksmen are Tel'Annas, Valhein, and Yorn.\n* Mage: Mages are sometimes known as \"AP Carry/APC\". These heroes deal lots of burst magic damage. Some mages tend to be fragile, while some mages tend to be more durable, depends on respective itemization. Mages are a mix of ranged heroes, which deal high amounts of burst damage from afar, or melee heroes, which deal lots of damage from close up, or a mixture of both.  Examples of mages are Lauriel, Liliana, and Tulen.\n* Assassin: These are heroes that are designed to deal large amounts of damage quickly, and often do not have much health. This hero type often searches for the marksman or mage from the enemy team, as well as any other fragile heroes, and also being responsible to shut down any enemy unit that is on a killing spree. They have high mobility and burst damage in order to be able to strike at valuable targets on the oppositions team. Examples of assassins are Murad, Nakroth, and Zill.\n* [[Tank (gaming)|Tank]]: Tanks are heroes that have large amounts of HP, and usually built completely defensive to be able to take damage for the team.  As a result, they often deal little damage. However, they often have abilities known as 'crowd control' that allow them to inhibit the movement of the enemy team. In addition to this, they can use these abilities to initiate a teamfight, or to prevent the enemy team from attacking high priority targets such as ally marksman or mage. Examples of tanks are Xeniel, Thane, and Toro.\n* Warrior:  Heroes that blend the attributes of damage dealer and tank, combining moderate survivability with respectable damage. Warriors usually have balanced amount of health, defenses, and attack damage, which is common designation for close-range melee duelist. Thus, they able to survive in a long period of fight and excel in doing continuos sustain damage. This type of heroes are also great against all odds, and tend to be extremely strong in 1v1 scenario. Examples of warriors are Florentino, Rourke, and Omen.\n* Support: Heroes whose abilities aid the rest of the team by providing healing, buffing allies (such as movement speed buffs), debuffing the enemy team (such as stunning), or a combination of the above. Support heroes are often paired with the marksman in the early laning phase of the game where the support doesn't require to kill minions, but instead focuses on aiding their partner and harassing the enemy heroes. Support heroes usually aids ally marksman as they are often weaker during the early phase of the game and need assistance in order to survive. Example of supports are Alice, Annette, and Krizzix.\n\nPlayers can purchase items, which make a large impact on the hero stats and playstyle. An example of this is Zephys, a dual warrior/assassin class. He have a passive ability that make him increase damage reduction against incoming damage to him based on the percentage of the amount of health loss. If only offensive items are bought, he will deal a lot of damage but has low amount of health and defenses, and may not survive for long. If Zephys purchase a mix of offensive and defensive items, he can soak damage for the team while he still be able to deal noticable amount of damage. If Zephys buy only defensive items, he can boost his damage reduction passive to its maximum potential, being literally almost impossible to die in most circumstances, but he will deal drastically low amount of damage.\n\nThis kind of playstyle can be applied to all heroes, allowing tanks to act as warriors, or for mages to act as supports, and vice versa.\n\n== History and development ==\n''Arena of Valor'' (formerly ''Strike of Kings'') is an international adaptation of ''[[Wangzhe Rongyao|Honor of Kings]]'' for markets outside mainland China. In 2015, Tencent approached [[Riot Games]] and asked them to turn their popular [[multiplayer online battle arena]] (MOBA) game ''[[League of Legends]]'' into a mobile title. However, Riot Games declined and claimed that the gameplay of ''League of Legends'' could not be replicated on smartphones. Tencent then proceeded to create their own mobile MOBA game, ''[[Wangzhe Rongyao]]'', roughly translated to English as ''Honor of Kings'', and was released in November 26, 2015. Nevertheless, several Riot Games employees deemed that the design of characters and abilities in ''Honor of Kings'' were \"blatantly ripping off the intellectual property of ''League of Legends''\", and reportedly brought these concerns to Tencent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.techinasia.com/chinas-top-mobile-game-complete-league-legends-ripoff|title=China top mobile game  is a complete League of Legends ripoff|last=Custer|first=Christopher|date=July 27, 2016|website=Tech in Asia|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Tencent then responded that they would changing its own game enough to sell as a standalone product with no relation to ''League of Legends''. Despite this, ''Honor of Kings'' already gained massive popularity in China at this point. Tencent felt its too late to make huge changes to the game, so Tencent decided that ''Honor of Kings'' will only go through small necessary changes while the international release of the game outside mainland China will be the one that featuring different contents, hence leading to the creation of ''Arena of Valor''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dotesports.com/league-of-legends/news/riot-strained-relationship-tencent-declining-players-mobile-games-information-32079|title=Riot\u2019s relationship with Tencent has reportedly been strained over declining profits and mobile games|last=Mickunas |first=Aaron |website=dotesports|access-date=2018-08-21}}</ref> \n\n''Arena of Valor'' is developed by [[TiMi Studios]] with the same engine and UI design as ''Honor of Kings'' and published by [[Tencent Games]] for western marketing, with [[Garena]] joined the development as they helped to westernize the atmosphere of the game. The in-game characters have been swapped from characters inspired by [[Chinese folklore]] [[Chinese mythology|and mythology]], to characters inspired by [[European folklore]] and some [[mythology|mythologies from other nations]] with blend a variety of elements including [[Lovecraftian horror]], [[steampunk]], [[high fantasy]], and [[sword and sorcery]] to appeal audiences outside mainland China, with the appearance of in-game characters mostly recycled but with fresh revamped designs of characters from ''[[Heroes of Newerth]]'', a MOBA game that Garena had acquired from [[S2 Games]]. Thus, this made ''Arena of Valor'' a [[spiritual successor]] to ''Heroes of Newerth''. \n\n''Arena of Valor'' also included several characters such as Butterfly, Violet, and Mina from ''Age of Gunslingers'' ({{zh|s=\u69cd\u795e\u7d00|c=|t=|p=Qi\u00e1ngsh\u00e9nj\u00ec}}), a [[Third-person shooter]] (TPS) game that was also developed by Tencent and TiMi Studios. In spite of that, the aforementioned characters have different lore than the game they originally hailed from.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/AgeOfGunslingersOnline|title=Age of Gunslingers|last=|first=|date=March 8, 2018|website=TVTropes|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://baike.baidu.com/item/%E6%9E%AA%E7%A5%9E%E7%BA%AA/6657145|title=Age of Gunslingers (\u67aa\u795e\u7eaa)|last=|first=|date=March 21, 2012|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=wuTa3XbRgZU&t=24s|title=\u5200\u92d2\u5bf6\u8c9d\u3001\u7f8e\u5a1c \u300a\u69cd\u795e\u7d00\u300b\u52d5\u756bPV\u3001\u89d2\u8272\u4ecb\u7d39\u4e32\u71d2\uff01\uff01Strike of Kings\uff08\u50b3\u8aaa\u5c0d\u8a23x\u69cd\u795e\u7d00)|last=|first=|date=March 3, 2017|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Additionally, ''Arena of Valor'' had multiple collaboration with other franchises, including having [[Crossover (fiction)|crossovers]] with [[DC Universe]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bluemoongame.com/what-are-dc-characters-doing-in-arena-of-valor/|title=What are DC characters doing in Arena of Valor?|last=|first=|date=November 15, 2017|website=Blue Moon Game|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://comicbook.com/gaming/amp/2018/04/19/tencent-interview-superman-arena-of-valor-mobile-80th-anniversary/|title=Exclusive Interview: Tencent Talks Superman\u2019s Debut In Arena of Valor, In Time For His 80th Anniversary.|last=|first=|date=April 18, 2018|website=comicbook.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://criticalindex.net/arena-of-valor-completes-dc-character-line-up-flash-joins-the-battle-b992e5fb814e|title=Arena of Valor completes DC characters line up|last=|first=|date=August 5, 2018|website=criticalindex.net|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> and ''Wiro Sableng'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://id.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wiro_Sableng|title=Wikipedia (Indonesian language) - Wiro Sableng|last=|first=|date=December 21, 2006|website=Wikipedia|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://esports.id/arena-of-valor/news/2018/07/1baff70e2669e8376347efd3a874a341/wujudkan-nuansa-lokal-wiro-sableng-hadir-di-arena-of-valor|title=Wujudkan nuansa lokal,Wiro Sableng hadir di Arena of Valor|last=|first=|date=July 27, 2018|website=Esports ID|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/life/2018/10/14/wiro-sableng-game-now-available-on-taiwan-aov-servers.html|title=Wiro Sableng now available in Taiwan server|last=|first=|date=October 14, 2018|website=The Jakarta Post|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://samurai-gamers.com/arena-of-valor/who-is-wiro-sableng/|title=Who is Wiro Sableng?|last=|first=|date=September 11, 2018|website=Samurai Gamers|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> and collaborated with [[KFC]] to advertising the game, notably in Taiwan and Thailand,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pocketgamer.biz/asia/news/72538/arena-of-valor-kfc-colonel-sanders-deal/|title=Arena of Valor confirmed having partnership with KFC.|last=|first=|date=March 6, 2020|website=Pocket Gamer|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> with [[Colonel Sanders]] made his appearance in the game as a skin for Ormarr.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oneesports.gg/aov/kfcs-colonel-sanders-is-now-a-playable-character-in-arena-of-valor/|title=KFC's Colonel Sanders made his appearance in Arena of Valor|last=|first=|date=February 13, 2020|website=ONE Esports|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nOriginally, Tencent actually intended to feature [[Marvel Comics]]'s characters during the earliest development stage of the game before they collaborated with [[DC Comics]], and has Close Beta Test (CBT) of the game under the name of ''Marvel Super Heroes MOBA'' ({{zh|s=\u8d85\u7ea7\u6218\u573a|c=|t=|p=Ch\u0101oj\u00ed zh\u00e0nch\u01ceng}}). The game feature some characters from Tencent's IP such as Butterfly, Violet, Mina, Valhein, and Zanis having crossover with Marvel's characters.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=R3QAbaznQFI|title=[CLOSED] Heroes Spotlight {{!}} Marvel Super Heroes MOBA \u8d85\u7ea7\u6218\u573a|last=#VKMOBA|first=V.K|date=September 30, 2016|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> However, Marvel then took back their license, and Tencent had to shut down the game and restart the development from scratch, in which also resulted TiMi Studios have to redesign the game in which made how ''Arena of Valor'' currently looks like. Tencent then approached DC Comics for collaboration to include DC's characters as replacement.\n\nThe soundtrack for ''Arena of Valor'' is composed by American music artist Matthew Carl Earl, proving a different atmosphere compared to the original score with Chinese music instruments in ''Honor of Kings''.\n\n''Arena of Valor'' have wide variety of publishers for different regions. ''Arena of Valor'' was first launched in Taiwan on October 14, 2016 by Garena, following a two-week closed beta testing period.<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://www.4gamers.com.tw/news/detail/30437/garena-new-mobile-moba-game | title = Garena\u300a\u50b3\u8aaa\u5c0d\u6c7a\u300b\u63ed\u958b\u795e\u79d8\u9762\u7d17\uff0c\u5c01\u6e2c\u9810\u767b\u6d3b\u52d5\u5373\u65e5\u958b\u8dd1 | author = 4Gamers | language = Chinese | accessdate = January 5, 2018 | website = 4Gamers \u5b98\u65b9\u7db2\u7ad9}}</ref> On October 17, 2017, Garena launched ''Arena of Valor'' in Malaysia, Singapore, and Philippines, where majority of the gaming community are playing mobile games. Garena decided to combined these three countries in one server. In South Korea, the game was published by [[Netmarble]] on April 26, 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mmoculture.com/2017/03/penta-storm-netmarble-prepares-to-launch-its-first-mobile-moba-in-korea/|title=Netmarble preparing to launch Strike of Kings as Penta Storm in Korea|last=|first=|date=March 10, 2017|website=MMO Culture|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The game was released in European app stores by Tencent in August 10, 2017,<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://forum.sok.proximabeta.com/forum.php?mod=viewthread&tid=1124 | title = A Big Update is Coming: A Letter From the Producer \u2013 Game Updates \u2013  Arena of Valor Forum | author = Joseph | date = July 25, 2017 | accessdate = January 5, 2018 | work = Arena of Valor Forum | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180105233730/https://forum.sok.proximabeta.com/forum.php?mod=viewthread&tid=1124 | archive-date = January 5, 2018 | url-status = dead | df = mdy-all }}</ref> and was released in North and Latin American mobile app stores on December 19, 2017.<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://www.theverge.com/2017/12/18/16469736/tencent-arena-of-valor-honor-of-King-north-america-launch | title = Tencent is bringing China's biggest game to the rest of the world | first = Andrew | last= Webster | date = December 18, 2017 | accessdate = December 18, 2017 | work = [[The Verge]]}}</ref> On June 28, 2018, Tencent implemented \"Asia server\" unannounced. The server included Australia, New Zealand, Myanmar, Laos, Cambodia, and Brunei. In Japan, [[DeNA]] cooperated with Tencent to launch ''Arena of Valor'' on November 30, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://samurai-gamers.com/arena-of-valor/japan-preregistration-begins/|title=AoV Japan server pre-registration|last=|first=|date=November 6, 2018|website=Samurai Gamers|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nThe game was announced to be released for the [[Nintendo Switch]] console during the September 2017 [[List of Nintendo Direct presentations|Nintendo Direct presentation]].<ref name=\"NL cites Switch announcement\">{{cite web |url=http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2017/09/free-to-play_moba_arena_of_valor_is_fighting_towards_switch |date=September 14, 2017 |accessdate=August 21, 2018 |last=McFerran |first=Damien |website=[[Nintendo Life]] |title=Free-To-Play MOBA Arena Of Valor Is Fighting Towards Switch}}</ref> A closed beta became available for the platform between June and July 2018,<ref name=\"BlueMoonGame Switch beta announced\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bluemoongame.com/arena-of-valor-gets-to-switch-in-beta-now-and-a-new-hero-2/|title=Arena Of Valor Gets To Switch, In Beta Now, And A New Hero|last=Jevtic|first=Stevan|date=June 19, 2018|website=Blue Moon Game|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=June 19, 2018}}</ref> and participants received an exclusive in-game skin for one of the characters.<ref name=\"NL cites Switch beta\">{{cite web |url=http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2018/06/arena_of_valor_closed_beta_starts_on_28th_june_participants_receive_exclusive_in-game_skin |date=June 23, 2018 |accessdate=August 21, 2018 |last=Doolan |first=Liam |website=[[Nintendo Life]] |title=Arena Of Valor Closed Beta Starts On 28th June, Participants Receive Exclusive In-Game Skin}}</ref> The game is confirmed to launch on the platform in September 25, 2018.<ref name=\"NL cites Switch launch\">{{cite web |url=http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2018/08/free-to-play_moba_arena_of_valor_launches_on_switch_this_september |date=August 21, 2018 |accessdate=August 21, 2018 |last=Doolan |first=Liam |website=[[Nintendo Life]] |title=Free-To-Play MOBA Arena Of Valor Launches On Switch This September}}</ref>\n\nSpeaking to [[Engadget]], Tencent Games revealed the Nintendo Switch port of the game is enhanced and optimized for the platform, taking advantage of the console's processing power and hardware features to implement various changes to the game, such as improved graphics and animations, better lighting, smoother lines, and additional minute details like butterflies. Additionally, several adjustments were made to the game to be playable on a bigger screen with traditional controls, and characters' stats have been reconfigured. Because of these changes, cross-play between the Nintendo Switch and mobile versions of the game is not possible. Tencent Games also have plans for competitive events based on the Nintendo Switch version.<ref name=\"Engadget interview\">{{cite web |url=https://www.engadget.com/2018/08/23/arena-of-valor-switch-interview-esports/ |date=August 23, 2018 |accessdate=August 27, 2018 |last=Conditt |first=Jessica |publisher=[[Engadget]] |title='Arena of Valor' is a completely different game on Switch}}</ref>\n\nRiot Games implied that their relationship with Tencent is still strong, and the conflict between them and their games is simply just \"a bump in the road\". In 2017, Riot Games filed a lawsuit against [[Moonton]], the developer of the mobile game ''[[Mobile Legends: Bang Bang]]'', because of copyright infringement, citing similarities between ''Mobile Legends'' and ''League of Legends''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://straatosphere.com/riot-games-sues-mobile-legends-developer/amp/|title=Riot Games sues League of Legends copycat|last=|first=|date=July 11, 2017|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.akshonesports.com/article/2017/07/riot-games-suing-shanghai-moonton-technology-copyright-infringement|title=Riot Games suing Moonton for copyright infringement|last=|first=|date=July 11, 2017|website=Akshon Esports|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The case was initially dismissed in Central District Court of California in United States on account of ''[[forum non conveniens]]''. Tencent, as Riot's parent company, on behalf of Riot Games, then filed a new, separate lawsuit directly targeting Moonton's CEO, Watson Xu Zhenhua in a Chinese court, which ruled in Tencent's favor in July 2018, awarded Tencent {{US$|2.9&nbsp;million|long=no}} ([[Renminbi|RMB]]19.4 million) in term of damages.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://dotesports.com/league-of-legends/news/source-riot-games-parent-tencent-wins-lawsuit-mobile-legends-31079 |title=Riot Games parent Tencent wins $2.9 million in lawsuit against Moonton CEO |first=Aaron |last=Mickunas |date=July 18, 2018 |website=[[Dot Esports]] |access-date=November 24, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190711104720/https://dotesports.com/league-of-legends/news/source-riot-games-parent-tencent-wins-lawsuit-mobile-legends-31079 |archive-date=July 11, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/gaming/news/riot-games-tencent-wins-lawsuit-league-of-legends-copy-1202878322/ |title=Tencent Wins Lawsuit Over 'League of Legends' Copycat |first=Liz |last=Lanier |date=July 19, 2018 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |access-date=November 24, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330075502/https://variety.com/2018/gaming/news/riot-games-tencent-wins-lawsuit-league-of-legends-copy-1202878322/ |archive-date=March 30, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> In addition, with both ''Honor of Kings'' and ''Arena of Valor'' still continuosly increasing popularity, playerbase, and have huge esports scene, Riot Games then realized and acknowledged the potential of mobile market for MOBA genre. Riot Games eventually announced their own mobile MOBA game, ''[[League of Legends: Wild Rift]]'' on October 16, 2019, which is 10th year anniversary of ''League of Legends''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/platform/amp/2019/10/15/20915315/league-of-legends-wild-rift-mobile-console-launch|title=League of Legends coming to mobile & console|last=|first=|date=October 15, 2019|website=The Verge|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Esports==\n===International competition===\n''Arena of Valor'' tournaments have been held in numerous regions, and each regions have their own local leagues such as Garena Challenger Series Pro League (GCS) in Taiwan,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=PEygJPtP4lM|title=AoV GCS Summer 2017 Highlights|last=|first=|date=October 11, 2017|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://liquipedia.net/arenaofvalor/Garena_Challenger_Series/2020/Spring|title=Garena Challenger Series Spring 2020|last=|first=|date=February 15, 2020|website=Liquipedia.net|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Realm of Valor Pro League (RPL) in Thailand,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=PEygJPtP4lM|title=Realm of Valor Pro League Summer 2020|last=|first=|date=January 31, 2020|website=Liquipedia.net|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Arena of Glory (AOG) in Vietnam,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://liquipedia.net/arenaofvalor/Arena_of_Glory/2019/Spring|title=Arena of Glory Spring 2019|last=|first=|date=February 23, 2019|website=Liquipedia.net|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Arena of Valor Star League (ASL) in Indonesia,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://liquipedia.net/arenaofvalor/AOV_Star_League/Season_4|title=Arena of Valor Star League Season 4|last=|first=|date=April 27, 2020|website=Liquipedia.net|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Arena of Valor: Valor Cup (AVC) in Malaysia, Singapore and Philippines,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://samurai-gamers.com/arena-of-valor/malaysia-first-aov-valor-cup-details/|title=AoV First Valor Cup details.|last=|first=|date=March 2, 2018|website=Samurai Gamers|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Arena of Valor: Valor Series (AVS) in Europe, North America, and Latin America,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.invenglobal.com/articles/7459/tencents-valor-series-season-3-starts-this-weekend-in-arena-of-valor-tournament-structure-detailed|title=Arena of Valor: Valor Series  Season 3|last=|first=|date=February 1, 2019|website=INVEN Global|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> and Arena of Valor Japan League (AJL) in Japan.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://liquipedia.net/arenaofvalor/Arena_of_Valor_Japan_League/2020/Spring|title=Arena of Valor Japan League Spring 2020|last=|first=|date=March 7, 2020|website=Liquipedia.net|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=u0LPcJu5Y5U&t=28s|title=\u3010 \u4f1d\u8aac\u5bfe\u6c7a -Arena of Valor-\u3011Arena of Valor Japan League \u6625\u306e\u9663 \u6c7a\u52dd\u6226|last=|first=|date=March 28, 2020|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n''Arena of Valor'' also have world championship tournament under the name of Arena of Valor International Championship (AIC) and Arena of Valor World Cup (AWC). Both are annual tournament. The difference between the two is AIC is a tournament that teams from across the world participate to earn profit and glory for their own team, while AWC is a tournament that teams from across the world participate to represent their own country.\n\nArena of Valor International Championship (AIC) that was first held in 2017, the event attracted more than 36,000,000 online viewers, breaking mobile game records worldwide and has since became the leading standard of mobile eSports. The game occupying the top positions of mobile game rankings in Asia for months has also received the honor of Google Play\u2019s Best of 2017 Game award in Europe.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamerbraves.com/arena-of-valor-brings-world-cup-2018-to-los-angeles/|title=Arena of Valor International Championship (AIC) that was first held in 2017, the event attracted more than 36,000,000 online viewers, breaking mobile game records worldwide and has since became the leading standard of mobile eSports.|last=|first=|date=April 22, 2017|website=Gamer Braves|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The second AIC tournament, was held in Thailand, from November 23, 2018 till December 16, 2018. The competiton featured more teams than the first year, increased to 16 teams from different regions to battle it out, competing for the title and a portion prize pool of $600,000 (\u00a3460,000).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://esportsinsider.com/2018/10/arena-of-valor-announces-international-championship/|title=Arena of Valor announces international championship|last=|first=|date=October 19, 2018|website=Esports Insider|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> \n\nThe first Arena of Valor World Cup (AWC) tournament was held in Los Angeles, United States, from July 17, 2018 till July 28, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamerbraves.com/arena-of-valor-brings-world-cup-2018-to-los-angeles/|title=Arena of Valor brings World Cup 2018 to Los Angeles|last=|first=|date=May 26, 2018|website=GamerBraves|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> A total prize pool of $500,000 made AWC as one of the largest-scale mobile eSports tournaments in gaming history. A total of nine regions competed for the grand prize which includes Taiwan - Hong Kong - Macau, Thailand, Vietnam, Malaysia - Singapore - Philippines, Indonesia, South Korea, North America, Latin America and Europe. Additionally, the tournament host selected three Wildcard teams to participate in AWC.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://liquipedia.net/arenaofvalor/Arena_of_Valor_World_Cup/2018|title=Arena of Valor World Cup 2018|last=|first=|date=July 17, 2018|website=Liquipedia|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The second AWC tournament, was held in Danang, Vietnam, from June 27, 2019 till July 14, 2019, with the same total prize pool of $500,000 just like the first AWC.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://esportsobserver.com/aov-2019-world-cup-vietnam/|title=AoV 2019 World Cup will be held in Vietnam|last=|first=|date=February 27, 2019|website=The Esports Observer|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://egg.network/news/arena-valor-world-cup-2019-will-be-hosted-vietnam-usd500000-prize-pool|title=AWC 2019 will be hosted in Vietnam with US$500,000 prize pool|last=|first=|date=May 13, 2019|website=egg.network|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The second AWC also marks Japan\u2019s first participation in an ''AOV'' international tournament since the game introduced their Japanese server in November 30, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gameishard.gg/aov/arena-of-valor-world-cup-2019-announces-12-teams-to-compete-for-usd-500000-prize-pool/amp/|title=Arena of Valor World Cup 2019|last=|first=|date=April 24, 2019|website=Game Is Hard|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dotesports.com/mobile/news/vietnam-wins-the-arena-of-valor-world-cup-2019/|title=Vietnam wins the Arena of Valor World Cup 2019|last=|first=|date=July 15, 2019|website=dotesports.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n===Asian Games 2018===\n{{Main|Arena of Valor at the 2018 Asian Games}}\n\n''Arena of Valor'' are part of electronic sports demonstration event in [[Asian Games]] 2018 held in Indonesia. Eight countries are able to participate after qualified from their respective regional qualification with Indonesia automatically qualifies as host. Unlike other electronic sports event, there is no qualification for Central and West Asia.<ref>{{cite news |title=AESF Game Result |url=https://www.aesf.com/images/Game_Result.pdf |accessdate=11 July 2018 |publisher=Asian Electronic Sports Federation |date=11 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180831012203/https://www.aesf.com/images/Game_Result.pdf |archive-date=2018-08-31 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n===Southeast Asian Games 2019===\n{{Main|Esports at the 2019 Southeast Asian Games}}\n\n''Arena of Valor'' is among the games title to be included as a medal event at the [[2019 Southeast Asian Games]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.insidethegames.biz/articles/1077291/arena-of-valor-to-become-official-game-title-of-2019-southeast-asian-games-in-philippines|title=Arena of Valor become official game title of 2019 Southeast Asian Games in Philippines.|last=|first=|date=March 27, 2019|website=insidethegames.biz|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\n''Arena of Valor'' won the award for \"Best Music in a Casual/Social Game\" at the 15th Annual Game Audio Network Guild Awards, whereas its other nomination was for \"Best Original Instrumental\".<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.audiogang.org/awards/2017-awards/ | title = 2017 Awards | accessdate = April 16, 2018 | work = Game Audio Network Guild}}</ref> It was also nominated for \"Original Score \u2013 Video Game\" at the 2017 [[Hollywood Music in Media Awards]],<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/hollywood-music-media-awards-full-winners-list-1057748/item/original-score-tv-show-limited-series-1057712 | title = Hollywood Music in Media Awards: Full Winners List | date = November 17, 2017 | accessdate = March 14, 2018 | work = [[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref> for \"Original Dramatic Score, New IP\" at the [[NAVGTR Awards]],<ref>{{cite web | url = https://navgtr.org/2018/03/13/horizon-wins-7-mario-goty/ | title = Winner List for 2017: Mario, Horizon | date = March 13, 2018 | accessdate = November 6, 2019 | work = [[NAVGTR Awards|National Academy of Video Game Trade Reviewers]]}}</ref> for \"Best Competitive Game\" at the 2018 [[Golden Joystick Awards]],<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/gaming/news/golden-joysticks-2018-nominees-announced-voting-open-now/ | title = Golden Joysticks 2018 nominees announced, voting open now | first = Tom | last = Hoggins | date = September 24, 2018 | accessdate = October 7, 2018 | newspaper = [[The Daily Telegraph]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.gamesradar.com/golden-joystick-awards-2018-winners/ | title = Golden Joystick Awards 2018 winners: God of War wins big but Fortnite gets Victory Royale | first = Connor | last = Sheridan | date = November 16, 2018 | accessdate = November 17, 2018 | work = [[GamesRadar+]]}}</ref> and for \"Fan Favorite Mobile Game\" at the [[Gamers' Choice Awards]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://file770.com/2018-gamers-choice-awards-nominees/ | title = 2018 Gamers' Choice Awards Nominees | first = Mike | last = Glyer | date = November 19, 2018 | accessdate = January 15, 2019 | work = File 770}}</ref> ''Arena of Valor: Flip the World'' won the award for \"Song/Score - Mobile Video Game\" at the [[9th Hollywood Music in Media Awards]],<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.hmmawards.com/2018-hmma-winners/ | title = 2018 HMMA WINNERS | date = November 14, 2018 | accessdate = November 15, 2018 | work = [[Hollywood Music in Media Awards]]}}</ref> while the game itself and ''Honor of Kings 2.0'' were nominated for the same category at the 10th Hollywood Music in Media Awards.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.shootonline.com/spw/hollywood-music-media-awards-announces-nominees | title = Hollywood Music In Media Awards Announces Nominees | date = November 4, 2019 | accessdate = November 6, 2019 | work = [[Shoot (advertising magazine)|Shoot]]}}</ref> The game was also nominated for \"Best Mobile Sport\" at the ''[[Pocket Gamer]]'' Mobile Games Awards,<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.mobilegamesawards.com/winners-2020/ | title = The winners of 2020 | accessdate = January 30, 2020 | work = [[Pocket Gamer]]}}</ref> while ''Honor of Kings 2.0'' was nominated for \"Best Sound Design in a Causal/Social Game\" and \"Best Music in a Casual Game\" at the 18th Annual Game Audio Network Guild Awards;<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.thehypemagazine.com/2020/02/game-audio-network-guild-announces-18th-annual-g-a-n-g-award-nominees/ | title = Game Audio Network Guild Announces 18th Annual G.A.N.G. Award Nominees | first = Kelly | last = Wilson | date = February 13, 2020 | accessdate = February 27, 2020 | work = The Hype Magazine}}</ref> however, the latter event was postponed to a later date due to concerns over the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/gdc-postponed-coronavirus-concerns-1281672 | title = Game Developers Conference \"Postponed\" Amid Coronavirus Concerns  |first = Patrick | last = Shanley | date = February 28, 2020 | accessdate = February 29, 2020 | work = [[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{notelist}}\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|https://www.arenaofvalor.com/}}\n\n{{Tencent Holdings}}\n\n[[Category:2017 video games]]\n[[Category:Android (operating system) games]]\n[[Category:IOS games]]\n[[Category:Multiplayer online battle arena games]]\n[[Category:Nintendo Switch eShop games]]\n[[Category:Tencent]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in China]]\n[[Category:Video games based on DC Comics]]\n[[Category:Unity (game engine) games]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguated:NA\u2192North America", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arena_of_Valor"}
{"title_page": "Bonda Meedum", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2012}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name           = Bonda Meedum\n| show_name_2    = [[Sinhala language|Sinhala]]: \u0db6\u0ddc\u0db3 \u0db8\u0dd3\u0daf\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca  \n| image          = Official Poster for Bonda Meedum (Teledrama).jpg\n| caption        = Official Poster for ''Bonda Meedum (Teledrama)''\n| network        = [[Independent Television Network]]\n| director       = Chandika Wijayasena\n| producer       = Upul Jayasinghe with Independent Television Network\n| writer         = \n| starring       = [[Udari Warnakulasooriya]]<br>[[Saranga Disasekara]]<br>Gayan Wickramathilaka<br>[[Buddhadasa Vithanarachchi]]   <br>[[Janak Premalal]]<br>Madani Malwatta<br>Piumi Purasinghe<br>Meena Kumari<br>[[Ananda Wickramage]]<br>Akila Sandakelum\n| num_episodes   = 250\n| genre          = [[Romance film|Romance]]<br>[[Comedy]]\n| picture_format = [[4:3]] [[Standard-definition television|(SDTV)]] (original broadcast)\n| audio_format   = [[Monaural|Mono]]\n| first_aired    = 15 September 2010\n| last_aired     = 2 September 2011\n| preceded_by    = [[Ithin Eeta Passe]]\n| followed_by    = [[Sihina Piyapath]]\n| runtime        = Monday to Friday at 8:30pm\n| country        = [[Sri Lanka]]\n| language       = [[Sinhala language|Sinhala]]\n| website        = http://www.v2.itn.lk/?p=342\n| website_title  = Official website {{in lang|en}}\n}}\n'''''Bonda Meedum''''' ([[Sinhala language|Sinhala]]: \u0db6\u0ddc\u0db3 \u0db8\u0dd3\u0daf\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca) is a [[Sri Lanka]]n television drama based on [[Bonda Meedum]], a popular series of novels created by Sri Lankan writer Sujeewa Prasanna Arachchi. The series debuted on 15 September, 2010 and concluded on 2 September 2011. [[Independent Television Network]] was the official broadcaster for Bonda Meedum. Screening at the 8.30 pm slot, the teledrama exceeded even the popularity of the novels. [[Udari Warnakulasooriya]] and [[Saranga Disasekara]] were awarded most popular female and male actors of the year, respectively, at the 16th Sumathi Tele Awards 2011.<ref name=awards>{{cite web |url=http://www.thurunu.com/2011/11/23/16th-sumathi-tele-awards-2011/ |title=16th Sumathi Tele Awards 2011 &#124; Thurunu.com Unlimited Entertainment World |publisher=Thurunu.com |date= |accessdate=2012-08-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120514025902/http://www.thurunu.com/2011/11/23/16th-sumathi-tele-awards-2011/ |archive-date=14 May 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Story==\n{{copyedit |date=April 2020}}\nDhanuka([[Saranga Disasekara]]) is a handsome boy in his early twenties. He lives in [[Matale]] with his parents and sister. Due to their poverty, at the end of his school education he comes to [[Colombo]]. His father sends him to Senarath Maliyadde in order to get a job in his company. Senarath Maliyadde([[Buddhadasa Vithanarachchi]]) who lives in [[Nawala]] is a rich businessman and also a good friend of Dhanuka's father.\n\nSansala([[Udari Warnakulasooriya]]), Maliyadde's only daughter, is a beautiful proud girl in her late teenage. She just has her father and younger brother named Kasun. She received a marriage proposal from her aunt's son Saliya. She show little interest in Saliya. She spends her life happily but is sometimes maudlin about the death of her mother.\n\nAfter a long and arduous journey, Dhanuka arrives unheralded at Maliyadde's home.  Sansala opens the door to him and, considering him a perfect stranger, starts to question and blame him.  Dhanuka falls for her instantly. Maliyadde being out at the time and brother and sister knowing nothing of him, they leave Dhanuka at the gate notwithstanding a heavy downpour and he and his belongings are soaked. Maliyadde returns home in his car, spots Dhanuka by the gate and welcomes him in. So the tale begins.However Sansala and Dhanuka get married blessings with both families.But Unfortunately,Sansala falls into a coma and she send to India for treatments for a year.So,Dhanuka has to live without his wife.However,Sansala recovers from coma after a year.Finally,They lived happily.\n\n==Cast and characters==\n*[[Udari Warnakulasooriya]] as Sansala Rambukwella(nee`Maliyadda),Dhanuka's wife,Maliyadda's daughter,Dharmasena and Vimalas' daughter in-law.\n*[[Saranga Disasekara]] as Dhanuka Rambukwella,Dharmasena and Vimalas' son,Sansala's husband,Maliyadda's son in-law,Iroshani's brother.\n*Gayan Wickramathilaka as Saliya,Douglas and Charuni's son,Sansala and Kasuns' cousin brother,He loved Sansala for property.\n*[[Buddhadasa Vithanarachchi]] as Senarath Maliyadda,Sansala and Kasuns' father,Dhanuka's father in-law.\n*[[Janak Premalal]] as Dharmasena Rambukwella,Dhanuka and Iroshanis' father,Sansal's father in-law.\n*Madhani Malwaththa as Vimala Rambukwella,Dhanuka and Iroshanis' mother,Sansal's mother in-law.\n*Meena Kumari as Charuni,Maliyadda's sister,Saliya's mother,Sansala and Kasuns' paternal aunt.\n*[[Uddika Premarathna]] as Senaka,Dhanuka's best friend in his first job.\n*Thishuna Perera as Kasun Maliyadda,Sansala's younger brother.\n*[[Rajitha Hiran]] as Kumara, Male servant in Maliyadda house.\n*Gayana Sudharshani as Kamala, Female servant in Maliyadda house.\n*[[Ananda Wickramage]] as Douglas,Charuni's husband,Maliyadda's brother in-law,Saliya's father.\n*Piyumi Purasinghe as Iroshani Rambukwella,Dharmasena and Vimalas' daughter,Dhanuka's younger sister,Sansala's sister in-law.\n*[[Gihan Fernando]] as Palawaththe Victor \n*[[Gayesha Perera]] as Minoli\n*Sada Mihiri Amrasingha as Mayumi\n\n==Music==\n*Theme Song (By Amila Nadeeshani and Surendra Perera): [[Sinhala language|Sinhala]]: \u0db6\u0ddc\u0db3 \u0db8\u0dd3\u0daf\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca\n\n==Awards==\n* The most popular actress of the year (16th Sumathi Tele Awards 2011):<ref name=awards /> Udari Warnakulasuriya (Bonda Meedum)\n* The most popular actor of the year (16th Sumathi Tele Awards 2011):<ref name=awards /> Saranga Disasekara (Bonda Meedum)\n\n==Slogan==\n