er's Luck\"\n| \u2014\n| rowspan=\"4\" | ''Gumboot Soup''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"All Is Known\"\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"The Last Oasis\"\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Greenhouse Heat Death\"\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Rolling Stoned\"\n| 2018\n| \u2014\n| ''Sketches of Brunswick East''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Cyboogie\"<br>\"Acarine\"\n| rowspan=\"7\" | 2019\n| \u2014\n| rowspan=\"3\" |''Fishing for Fishies''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Fishing for Fishies\"\n| 33\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Boogieman Sam\"\n| \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Planet B\" \n| \u2014\n|''Infest the Rats' Nest''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"The Bird Song\"\n|\u2014\n| ''Fishing for Fishies''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Self-Immolate\"\n| \u2014\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''Infest the Rats' Nest''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Organ Farmer\"\n|\u2014\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.discogs.com/artist/2532180-King-Gizzard-And-The-Lizard-Wizard Discography] at [[Discogs]]\n\n{{King Gizzard and the Lizard Wizard|state=uncollapsed}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:King Gizzard and the Lizard Wizard}}\n[[Category:Discographies of Australian artists]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Australian English|date=July 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{refimprove|date=November 2018}}\n{{Infobox artist discography\n| Artist = [[King Gizzard & the Lizard Wizard]]\n| Image = King Gizzard %26 the Lizard Wizard.jpg\n| Caption = Three-sevenths of the band onstage. From left to right: Cook Craig, Ambrose Kenny-Smith and Stu Mackenzie.\n| Studio = 15\n| Live = 3\n| EP = 2\n| Singles = 33\n| Music videos = 30\n}}\n\nThe [[discography]] for [[King Gizzard & the Lizard Wizard]], an Australian [[psychedelic rock]] band formed in 2010 in Melbourne, consists of fifteen [[studio album]]s, two [[extended play]]s and thirty-three [[single (music)|single]]s.\n\nThe band released their first two albums, ''[[12 Bar Bruise]]'' in 2012 and ''[[Eyes Like the Sky]]'' in 2013. Their third to eighth albums followed with ''[[Float Along \u2013 Fill Your Lungs]]'' in 2013, ''[[Oddments]]'' and ''[[I'm in Your Mind Fuzz]]'' in 2014, ''[[Quarters!]]'' and ''[[Paper M\u00e2ch\u00e9 Dream Balloon]]'' in 2015 and ''[[Nonagon Infinity]]'' in 2016. Nonagon Infinity marked the first time the group reached the top 20 in their home country, peaking at number nineteen in the [[ARIA|Australia Albums Chart]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/culture/music/album-reviews/king-gizzard-the-lizard-wizard-murder-of-the-universe-prog-rock-walks-the-earth-once-more-1.3120956|title=King Gizzard & the Lizard Wizard: Murder of the Universe \u2013 prog-rock walks the earth once more|last=Clayton-Lea|first=Tony|date=21 June 2017|work=[[The Irish Times]]|access-date=19 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.axs.com/top-10-best-king-gizzard-and-the-lizard-wizard-songs-115982|title=Top 10 best King Gizzard and The Lizard Wizard songs|last=Adams|first=Will|date=13 March 2017|website=[[AXS (company)|AXS]]|access-date=19 April 2018}}</ref> In 2017 released five studio albums within the year: ''[[Flying Microtonal Banana]]'' in February, ''[[Murder of the Universe]]'' in June, ''[[Sketches of Brunswick East]]'', a collaboration with the music project of Alex Brettin, [[Mild High Club]], in August, ''[[Polygondwanaland]]'', which was released into the public domain, in November, and ''[[Gumboot Soup]]'' in December. Over a year later, the band released their fourteenth studio album, ''[[Fishing for Fishies]]'' on 26 April 2019. Their fifteenth album, ''[[Infest the Rats' Nest]]'' was released on 16 August 2019.\n\n==Studio albums==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Title \n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"10\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| [[Music recording sales certification|Certifications]]<br /><small>([[List of music recording sales certifications|sales thresholds]])\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:80%;\"|[[ARIA Charts|AUS]]<br /><ref name=\"AUS Charts\">Australian charts:\n* ARIA Charts top&nbsp;50: {{cite web | url = http://www.australian-charts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=King+Gizzard+And+The+Lizard+Wizard | title = Discography King Gizzard and the Lizard Wizard | website = australian-charts.com | accessdate = 17 January 2018 }}\n* ''I'm in Your Mind Fuzz'': {{cite journal | date = 17 November 2014 | archiveurl = http://pandora.nla.gov.au/pan/23790/20141119-1122/Issue1290.pdf | title = Week Commencing ~ 17th November 2014 ~ Issue #1290 | last = Wallace | first = Ian | work = The ARIA Report | format = PDF | publisher = [[Australian Recording Industry Association]] (ARIA) | issue = 1290 | pages = 2, 6, 14, 21 | url = http://www.aria.com.au/pages/documents/issue1290.pdf | archivedate = 19 November 2014 | accessdate = 17 January 2018 }}\n* ''Quarters!'': {{cite journal | date = 1 June 2015 | archiveurl = http://pandora.nla.gov.au/pan/23790/20150602-0000/Issue%201318.pdf | title = Week Commencing ~ 1st June 2015 ~ Issue #1318 | last = Wallace | first = Ian | work = The ARIA Report | format = PDF | publisher = Australian Recording Industry Association (ARIA) | issue = 1318 | page = 8 | url = http://www.aria.com.au/pages/documents/issue1318.pdf | archivedate = 2 June 2015 | accessdate = 17 January 2018 }}\n* ''Paper M\u00e2ch\u00e9 Dream Balloon'': {{cite journal | date = 30 November 2015 | archiveurl = http://pandora.nla.gov.au/pan/23790/20151202-0000/Issue1344.pdf | title = Week Commencing ~ 30th November 2015 ~ Issue #1344 | last = Wallace | first = Ian | work = The ARIA Report | format = PDF | publisher = Australian Recording Industry Association (ARIA) | issue = 1344 | pages = 6, 8, 21 | url = http://www.aria.com.au/pages/documents/issue1344.pdf | archivedate = 2 December 2015 | accessdate = 17 January 2018 }}\n</ref><ref name=\"AUS Charts 2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au